Defendant Anthony Lee Roach in court with attorney Alexis B Stewart.  Defendant Anthony Lee Roach in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.   Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    The Court imposed the following sentence:   The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 4 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 years with credit for 74 days time served.  Defendant shall serve two (2) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but IS eligible for  the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample if not previously taken.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay restitution to Ms. Dorothy S. in the stipulated amount of $1,190.00 to be paid first; plus the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  All monies are to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No contact with Ms. Dorothy S.;
 - No contact with WalMart at 10330 West Silverspring Drive, Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay any balances remaining of the restitution,  DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Restitution Worksheet;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
